State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The big Dwarven Magettas are firebreathing powerfull automatons that patrol the now abandoned Dwarven ruins. Lighter and less armored than a Centurion, what a Magetta loses in defence and offensive raw strength, it gains in agility, mobility and fire power. Also being composed internally by lava, they produce a tremendous  heat around them.
State.Name: Dwarven Magetta- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dragon ball'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ettins are hulking, two-headed abominations with an immense hatred for all living things. Descendants of a tribe of Ogres cursed by Malacath himself in ancient times, these tormented beasts of incredible strength but limited intellect are everything an adventurer doesn't want to encounter.
State.Name: Ettins - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail and DungeonMasterEli
State.Description: Gravelords are enigmatic entities formed by hundreds of darkened bones covered in a cloak of dense shadows. They're the spawn of Sithis, the representation of the primordial state of emptiness and the Void. They roam the darkest places of Nirn and Oblivion, surrounded by their dread armies of scary Gravelord Servants.
State.Name: Gravelords- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dark souls'')

Original.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt (SE) 1.4.1 version-27520-1-4-1-1651832785.rar

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Old Gods of the Hunt are powerfull and mysterious ancient creatures from a previous Wild Hunt, that still roams through Tamriel in very small numbers in the current era. Ferocious and stunning powerfull, this Wild Hunt beasts are connected to Hircine, and worshiped since the beginning by the Reachmen and the Bosmer as one of their Old Gods.
State.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''the witcher'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ogrims are a type of ogre-like enormous daedra with very little intellect and enormous raw power. They are sent into the mortal world to menace living things for the amusement of the Daedric Princes, and are mostly associated with Malacath. Many scholars even speculate them to be a daedric corruption of the Ogres made by Malacath himself.
State.Name: Ogrim- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''daedra'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: You can now hear blowflies flying around rotting corpses, whether human or animal. Without a doubt, your world will have an extra touch of realism, immersion and it will also become a little more disgusting.
State.Name: Flies Around Corpses- Mihail's Shards of Immersion (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Crystal Golems are large masses of faceless and vaguely humanoid crystal, animated by unknown means, that patrol Blackreach. Despite Azura's Moonshadow and Meridia's Colored Rooms being almost inaccessible to mortals, it's certain that some roam that realms since they're often summoned on Nirn by azura's and meridia's worshipers.
State.Name: Crystal Golems - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dark souls'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwarven Colossus are one of the magnum opus amongst the Dwemer Animunculi. Massive, and with incredible endurance and fire power, these machines possess specialized weapons on their arms, a large dual-blade gauntlet on the right and a hammer piston that creates fire pulses on the left. They are also able to breath extremely destructive fire.
State.Name: Dwarven Colossus - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dwemer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Created to be the pawns on the front line of the Dwemer army, Dwarven Defenders are articulated automatons designed to emulate the combat skills of their creators in wars and conflicts. Wielding light dwarven shields, and sledgehammers, and firing blasts of electricity through their central chest core, these machine armies are a force to be feared.
State.Name: Dwarven Defenders- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dwemer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: One of the most impressive creations of the Dwemer are the Power Armors. When the Dwemer disappeared, they left behind all their arsenal, including their armored suits, over time, the Dwemer prodigious technological AI managed to hack and gain control over some of these extremely complex creations, re-engineering them into functional Automatons.
State.Name: Controlled Dwarven Power Suits - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dwemer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Designed for underwater drilling and maintenance work and resembling an enhanced dwemer diving suit, they're made of a thick metal carapace, specially reinforced against water pressure, with a head encased in a large hemispherical glass helmet studded with lit yellow portholes and a huge, fully-functional conical drill attached to the left-arm.
State.Name: Dwarven Driller- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''bioshock'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwemers used to adapt some of their war automatons to perform trivial functions. Some of them were Dwarven Ballistas who had their bolt launching platform removed, and in its place were installed sets of spinning blades typically used as traps in dwemer ruins. These modified automatons were used for harvesting and became known as Dwarven Threshers.
State.Name: Dwarven Threshers- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dwemer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ride into battle mounted on a legendary Falmeri Frost Mare, made of the purest magically enchanted ice adorned with the finest ivory, and created by the long time gone Snow Elf mages of old.
State.Name: Falmeri Frost Mare Mount- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Materialized from obscure childhood fears, what could be more frightening than a profound trauma turned into a solid, horrifying deformed infant form of flesh and blood, which returns from the past lost in time to torment those who tried to forget it at all costs?
State.Name: Grey Children- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''silent hill'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: High Clannfears are aggressive saurian humanoids from Oblivion, with large spike-covered bony crests adorning their heads, and with sharp beaks and long claws specially designed to tear their prey to shreds. Intelligent, but bordering on bestiality, they are often used and trained by higher Daedra as guard dogs.
State.Name: High Clannfears - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

Original.Name: High Clannfears - My textures SE by Xtudo - 2K-95906-1-1689424611.7z

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: These ferocious men-bull descendants of Morihaus are said to have symbolized the Alessian Empire during the 1st Era, but later became commonly seen as dangerous beasts by other races. The variant that inhabits Skyrim is among those closest to the original glory and power of its race, unlike other more ferocious variants that live across Tamriel.
State.Name: High Minotaurs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''eso'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Pitroamers are a type of terrestrial cetacean that can be found in deep caves, feeding on larvae, mushrooms and roots. Their closest relatives are the Orcas, with which they share some physical similarities, the most obvious being the shape of the head. Falmer are known to tame and ride Pitroamers.

State.Author: Mihail
